reviewText: BEST kernel mgr This beats all others. It started because the vibration intensity on my N6 was way too high, so I found this app. I saw the features for CPU, etc mgmt and looked for another app that maybe had better/expanded features but nope, this one is the BEST!! The simplicity, ease of use and options make this hands down my favorite. It reapplies my CPU & other settings on boot but doesn't keep my vibration intensity set for some reason (I think that's my ROM/kernel because it's worked in the past). 5/5 LOVE IT!!!

author: Dylan Woods
reviewText: Great for the most part.. I'm fairly new to this kernel editing and device changing. I always knew how to root and flash ROMs/recoveries/bootloaders. What I didn't realize was the capabilities, and added bonuses of modifying your internal hardware. The biggest advantage for me is CPU, it definitely improved my battery by lowering the frequencies and setting an interactive governor. Anyways, there seems to be one disadvantage at this time. After every reboot (with bootup restoration enabled) all of my customizations reset.

author: Abdul Hussain
reviewText: App freezes are now officially gone As the title says, since I have updated this app to 0.8.6, it gets stuck on 'Checking Requirements' on the LG G3 D855 running CyanogenMod 13 & the official LG G3 6.0 ROM, but this app works fine on the Samsung Galaxy S3 mini (GT-I8190) running CyanogenMod 12.1. >>> UPDATE: The issues are now fixed (version 0.8.6.4-20160119). Thank you Alexander Martinz for not only replying to my review in a civil manner, but most importantly, fixing the app.
